						               													<description>Somewhere in the hedegrows, Normandy, 1944&amp;hellip;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The artillery falls silent and you order your platoon to cross the hedgerow.  The men are jittery; most are replacements, on the frontline for less than a day.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rip of a German MG cuts through the air.  Screams follow and the battle is joined.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You step up to the firing line, to urge the green replacements forward and direct fire against the Germans.  Today might be your last.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is Row by Row, the first scenario/campaign back for A Sergeant&amp;rsquo;s War.  Players can use the pack for stand-alone games or as a series of linked scenarios, in which your casualties and victories have cumulative effects.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The book is written for A Sergeant&amp;rsquo;s War, but is playable with any WWII rules set.  The scenarios feature platoon-sized battles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The scenarios all play on 4&amp;rsquo;x4&amp;rsquo; or smaller tables (for 15mm/20mm scale) and usually feature 30-50 troops and several vehicles per side.  The book includes:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Historical Background&amp;#10;     Information for using the scenarios with other rules sets&amp;#10;     6 Scenarios, featuring bocage-fights, German counter attacks, and a two-part street battle&amp;#10;     Color maps &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
